        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 519 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Rock Hill, or 8 miles northwest of Richburg, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lesslie, Catawba, Edgemoor, and Rock Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
